text: Custer County is a county in the U.S. state of Oklahoma. It was named in honor of General George Armstrong Custer. As of 2020, 28,513 people lived there. Its county seat is Arapaho. == Geography == The county has a total area of 1,002 square miles. == References == Category:Oklahoma counties Category:1891 establishments in Oklahoma Territory
title: Custer County, Oklahoma
